sql:
SELECT e.employee_name, m.employee_name AS manager_name
FROM employees e
JOIN employees m ON e.manager_id = m.employee_id;

external_knowledge:
- Frequent buyers refer to customers who made more than one sale;
- Premium items are those priced above $100.00;
- Start of a quarter means the months January, April, July, and October.

sql:
SELECT commission_id, employee_id, sale_id, commission_amount, commission_date, commission_status
FROM commissions
WHERE employee_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "golden goose of sales" metaphorically refers to the employee with the highest sales in 2020;
- "nest egg" metaphorically represents the total sales amount, indicating the financial outcome or performance of the employee;
- "grow or shrink" metaphorically refers to the increase or decrease in sales from one year to the next.

sql:
SELECT employees.employee_name, sales.sale_amount
FROM employees
JOIN sales ON employees.employee_id = sales.employee_id;
